Citation.sTitle: Molar heat capacities of some aqueous 2-amino-2-hydroxymethyl-1,3-propanediol + glycol systems
Citation.sAbstract: A new set of molar heat capacity data for aqueous 2-amino-2-hydroxymethyl-1,3-propanediol 56 to 44 % by weight water, in a fixed amount of glycol - 40 % by weight) were gathered via reliable measurement method are presented in this report. The glycols considered were diethylene glycol (DEG), triethylene glycol (TEG), tetraethylene glycol (T4EG), propylene glycol (PG), dipropylene glycol (DPG) and tripropylene glycol (TPG). The 198 data points gathered fit excellently well the Redlich-Kister-type model for the temperature- and concentration-dependence of molar heat capacity for the different systems, with an overall AAD of 0.07 %.
